{% section
   backgroundColor="secondary"
   centered=true
   width="auto"
   height="auto" %}
## What to Bring to Camp

To help your camper have the best week possible, here's a comprehensive packing list for summer camp at Camp Otyokwah in Butler, Ohio.
{% /section %}

{% section
   backgroundColor="cream"
   centered=false
   width="auto"
   height="auto" %}
{% sectionHeading text="Essentials" level="2" align="center" /%}

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="Shirt"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Clothing"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Everyday wear**: 6-7 sets of casual clothes (t-shirts, shorts, sweats)
- **Sleepwear**: Pajamas for each night
- **Underwear & socks**: One pair for each day, plus extras
- **Modest swimsuit**: At least 2 (they may not dry overnight)
- **Warm layers**: Sweatshirt or jacket for cool evenings
- **Rain gear**: Light rain jacket or poncho
- **Closed-toe shoes**: Athletic shoes for activities
- **Water shoes or sandals**: For swimming and waterfront activities
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Bed"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Bedding & Linens"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Sleeping bag** or **twin sheets and blanket**
- **Pillow** and **pillowcase**
- **Towels**: 2-3 bath towels and 1-2 beach towels
- **Washcloth**

*Note: bunks are provided in cabins — just bring your bedding!*
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Droplet"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Toiletries"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Soap** and **shampoo**
- **Toothbrush** and **toothpaste**
- **Deodorant**
- **Sunscreen** (SPF 30+)
- **Bug spray**
- **Personal hygiene products**
- **Brush or comb**
- **Lip balm** with SPF
- **Trash bag/laundry bag** for dirty laundry
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Pill"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Medications"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- All medications (prescription and OTC) in **original containers**
- Give medications to the **camp nurse upon arrival**
- Include a written list of **dosages and times**
- Supplements **MUST** follow same procedure

*Camp nurse will dispense all medications/supplements according to your schedule.*
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

{% sectionHeading text="Recommended Items" level="2" align="center" /%}

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="Book"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Faith & Personal Items"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Bible** and **journal**
- **Reading materials** for quiet time
- **Stationery and stamps** for writing home
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Sun"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Outdoor Gear"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Water bottle** (reusable, labeled with name)
- **Flashlight** or **headlamp** with extra batteries
- **Backpack** or **daypack** for carrying items
- **Baseball cap** or **sun hat**
- **Sunglasses**
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Gamepad2"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Optional Fun Items"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Camera** (disposable or basic digital) — no pictures inside cabins please
- **Musical instruments** (acoustic only — check with camp first)
- **Playing cards** or **board games**
- **Stuffed animal** or **comfort item** for younger campers (or the young at heart)
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Wallet"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Money"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- A small amount of cash or prepaid funds may be useful for optional snack purchases
- **Do not bring large amounts of cash** — keep expensive items at home
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

{% sectionHeading text="What NOT to Bring" level="2" align="center" /%}

{% sectionCard variant="elevated" background="light" width="auto" %}
For the safety and benefit of all campers, please **DO NOT PACK** the following items:
{% /sectionCard %}

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="Smartphone"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Electronics"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- Cell phones (parents will be contacted if needed)
- Tablets, iPads, or laptops
- Handheld gaming devices
- Smart watches (basic watches are fine)
- Bluetooth speakers or headphones

*Help your camper disconnect from screens and connect with friends and God!*
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Ban"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Prohibited Items"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Weapons** of any kind (including pocket knives)
- **Alcohol, tobacco, vaping devices**, or **illegal substances**
- **Fireworks or explosives**
- **Inappropriate media** (movies, music, books with mature content)
- **Expensive jewelry** or **large amounts of cash**
- **Food or drinks** (dietary needs handled by camp kitchen — contact us to discuss)
- **Pets**
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}

{% sectionHeading text="Packing Tips" level="2" align="center" /%}

{% cardGrid cols="2" width="auto" height="auto" backgroundColor="" %}
{% contentCard
   icon="ClipboardCheck"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Before You Pack"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
1. **Label everything** with your camper's name (permanent marker or name labels)
1. **Pack in a duffel bag** rather than hard-sided luggage (easier to store in cabins)
1. **Use a checklist** while packing and have your camper help
1. **Keep medications separate** to hand directly to camp nurse
{% /contentCard %}

{% contentCard
   icon="Lightbulb"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Pro Tips"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
5. **Pack extra underwear and socks** — they have a way of disappearing!
1. **Don't overpack** — campers won't need a different outfit for every activity
1. **Include a stamped, addressed postcard** for your camper to send home
1. **Bring clothes that can get messy** — camp is an adventure!
{% /contentCard %}
{% /cardGrid %}
{% /section %}

{% sectionHeading text="What We Provide" level="2" align="center" /%}

{% sectionCard variant="default" background="none" width="auto" %}
You don't need to bring:

- **Meals and snacks** (please contact us if your child has specific dietary restrictions at [info@otyokwah.org](mailto:info@otyokwah.org))
- **Program equipment** (climbing harnesses, kayak gear, archery equipment, disc golf discs, etc.)
- **Life jackets** (available at waterfront)
- **Bedding frames** (bunks provided in cabins)
- **Toilet paper and hand soap** (provided in bathrooms)
{% /sectionCard %}

{% sectionHeading text="Lost & Found" level="2" align="center" /%}

{% contentCard
   icon="Search"
   iconSize="md"
   title="Labeling & Lost Items"
   headingLevel="3"
   width="auto"
   height="auto"
   backgroundColor="" %}
- **Label EVERYTHING** with your camper's full name
- Lost items are placed in the Lost & Found during camp
- Unclaimed items are **donated to charity 30 days after camp ends**
- Check the cabin and Lost & Found thoroughly before departure
{% /contentCard %}

{% sectionHeading text="Questions?" level="2" align="center" /%}

If you're unsure about whether to pack something specific, please contact us at [info@otyokwah.org](mailto:info@otyokwah.org) or call (419) 883-3854.

